articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Palestinians said the new aerial and ground offensives and forced evacuations were “ethnic cleansing.”
articles.title: Israeli attacks kill 23 people in Gaza, medics say, as ceasefire hopes dim

articles.author: Manuel Ausloos, Antony Paone
articles.description: People vented anger over what they perceived as as tardy alerts from the authorities and a late response by the emergency services when disaster struck.
articles.title: Protests over Spain flood response interrupt visit by king to stricken Valencia suburb

articles.author: Sarah Marsh, Andreas Rinke
articles.description: Germany's new leftist populist party aims to exact a high price from mainstream parties for helping them govern three eastern states: demanding that their regional officials join calls to stop arming Ukraine.
articles.title: Germany's upstart leftists chip at pro-Ukraine consensus

articles.author: Nandita Bose, James Oliphant
articles.description: Opinion polls show a historically close race, and both campaigns say they are not sure who will prevail in the seven states that are likely to determine the outcome.
articles.title: Harris campaigns in Michigan, Trump hits eastern battleground states

articles.author: James Oliphant, Nandita Bose
articles.description: Democrat Kamala Harris and Republican Donald Trump head to North Carolina on Saturday to try to clinch support in the southeastern battleground state just three days before Tuesday's U.S. presidential election.
articles.title: Trump, Harris head to North Carolina in US election campaign's final weekend

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Hundreds of opposition activists rallied in Belgrade on Sunday to protest over a deadly accident at a railway station in Serbia's north, for which they blame negligence and corruption by the authorities.
articles.title: Activists rally in Belgrade to protest railway station disaster

articles.author: Mohammed Salem
articles.description: After over a year of war in Gaza, Palestinian fishermen gather along the coastline, desperately casting their nets in hopes of catching enough for their families amid widespread hunger.
articles.title: Amid war and deep hunger, Gaza fisherman struggle to feed families

articles.author: Tom Balmforth, Alexander Tanas
articles.description: Moldovans vote on Sunday in a presidential runoff that has been overshadowed by election meddling allegations and could see Moscow gain more influence in a diplomatic battleground between Russia and the European Union.
articles.title: Moldova holds presidential runoff election amid claims of Russian meddling

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Europe will need to rethink its support of Ukraine if Donald Trump is elected president of the United States, Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban said on Sunday, as the continent "will not be able to bear the burdens of the war alone".
articles.title: Hungary's Orban says Trump victory would force Europe to rethink support for Ukraine

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Brazil's president fell at home in October and suffered a small brain hemorrhage and trauma to the back of his head
articles.title: Lula stable after follow-up tests for October head injury
